text:
recent upgrade to apache 2.2.21 from 2.2.19, when restarting apache it fails with

[Tue Oct 11 00:00:02 2011] [notice] Graceful restart requested, doing restart
httpd: Syntax error on line 96 of /usr/local/etc/apache22/httpd.conf: Cannot load /usr/local/libexec/apache22/mod_negotiation.so into server: /usr/local/libexec/apache22/mod_negotiation.so: Undefined symbol "ap_set_accept_ranges"

You upgraded httpd but not the modules you compiled?  How odd.

Please refer to the appropriate users@httpd.apache.org list for peer support,
bugzilla is strictly for reporting source code defects.
creator: wrowe@apache.org
